      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIGHTY MISS (5) showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 2.5 lengths over 500m Bendigo in 28.40. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Top chance in this line up. PAW LAMPADES (1) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing seventh (26.23) in a Grade 5 at Ballarat. Has ability and can atone. MADAM SERIOUS (2) missed the frame last time but had been racing well prior to that, winning a Mix 6/7 three back before a placing at Geelong the following run. Rates a winning chance on best. PYRENEES ACE (8) is always hard to beat when drawn in this box.",
